  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Schools for IDP Resettlement in Katakwi (SIRK) (Uganda)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Years of conflict has devastated the lives of children in Uganda&apos;s northern district of Katakwi. Traumatised by two decades of war, which destroyed communities and left many living in refugee camps, most children were also robbed of an education. As security improves and families return to their homes, this project works with the local government to ensure schools are equipped to meet the complex needs of children. This means more young people are given the chance to complete their education, recover from the effects or war and work towards sustainable and stable futures.</narrative>
  </description>
